NEW DELHI, India, January 5, 2017/APO/ --
                                                
                        President of Kenya His Excellency Uhuru Kenyatta will pay a State Visit to India from 10-12 January 2017 on an invitation extended by Prime Minister Narendra Modi. The two leaders will hold official talks on 11 January in New Delhi. During the visit President Kenyatta is also expected to call on the President. Indian dignitaries including the Vice President, Minister for Home Affairs and Minister for Defence are also expected to call on President Kenyatta. President Kenyatta is likely to be accompanied by several Ministers. He is expected to attend a business forum in Delhi on 12th forenoon.
Â 

President Kenyatta will also attend the Vibrant Gujarat Global Summit on 10 January 2017 at Gandhinagar and participate in business events.